      "message": "Can we just use two levels of sync.WaitGroup?  ie. add a `wg *sync.WaitGroup` field to the Work struct and do:\n\nfor w :\u003d range queue {\n  // For organizational purposes, create a step representing this batch,\n  // with the batch call to FM and any individual reruns all nested inside.\n  defer w.wg.Done()\n  ctx :\u003d startStep(w.Ctx, td.Props(strings.Join(w.Sources, \" \")))\n  defer endStep(ctx)\n  worker(ctx, w.Sources, w.Flags)\n}\n\nThen, in kickoff() we do:\n\nkickoff :\u003d func(...) {\n  wg.Add(1)\n  ...\n  var kickoffWg sync.WaitGroup // Pending Work for this instance of kickoff().\n  util.ChunkIter(len(sources), batchSize, func(start, end int) error {\n    kickoffWg.Add(1)\n    queue \u003c- \u0026Work{ctx, \u0026kickoffWg, sources[start:end], flags}\n    return nil\n  })\n  // Once all the work we\u0027ve kicked off finishes, signal that we\u0027re done.\n  go func() {\n    kickoffWg.Wait()\n    wg.Done()\n  }()\n}",
